Excalibur is a web interface built with Python that simplifies the extraction of tabular data from PDF files. It leverages the Camelot library to provide advanced table detection and extraction capabilities, supporting both line-based (Lattice) and whitespace-based (Stream) tables. Excalibur allows users to save extraction settings for consistent results across similar PDF documents and offers various output formats, ensuring a streamlined workflow for converting PDF tables into usable data.

The library aims to provide a declarative and type-safe approach to API client development.
